Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek, possibly Aeolian, grey ware pottery closed vessel, probably an oinochoe; exterior: dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The sherd joins British Museum 1888,0601.629 and 1888,0601.618. The fabric finds parallels with British Museum 1888,0601.637 which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn). The results placed the fabric (sample NAUK 64) in NAA group G and the origin was determined to be Aeolis.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.153)
